# Vibe Journal

This repository is **Vibe Journal** — a responsive static blog website with an editorial homepage, topic cards, searchable article previews, and a newsletter signup.

## Stack

- Plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript — no build step or framework
- Deployed via GitHub Pages from `main`
- Local dev: `python3 -m http.server 8000`

## Key files

- `index.html` — page structure and sample blog content
- `styles.css` — responsive layout and visual design
- `script.js` — mobile navigation, post filtering, newsletter form behavior
- `.github/workflows/pages.yml` — GitHub Pages deployment

## Conventions

- Keep the site static; avoid adding npm/build tooling unless explicitly requested
- Preserve accessibility: semantic HTML, ARIA labels, keyboard-friendly navigation
- Match the existing editorial tone and design language (Inter + Playfair Display)
- Test changes locally with a static server before committing
